postcontent:
9mm brass ammo from freedom munitions, remanufactured, 18 boxes 50ct, Price is firm. No trades. I can possibly deliver directly to you or meet you close by. I will not respond to offers for less than the stated price. Cash only. Will accept credit card with a 5% fee.

REDACTED / Justin

Freedom Munitions "Like-New" manufacturing process provides like-new ammo performance.
FREEDOM MUNITIONS inspects all cartridge cases for defects. The Scharch Range Master machines are fully automated and cases are checked for any debris and pressure tested for any splits or cracks. Primers are removed, flash holes are cleared, and primer pockets are reamed to accept new primers.
FREEDOM MUNITIONS then washes cases in an acid wash specially designed to remove all remaining burnt powder from the flash hole and interior of the case which tumbling doesn't remove. Then cases are tumbled in a dryer for a factory look and finish.
FREEDOM MUNITIONS roll sizes all cases on our own designed machines to meet S.A.A.M.I.specification. This method is the industry standard for commercial sizing, insuring the case wall is sized down to the rim which insures new component performance.
FREEDOM MUNITIONS then loads these processed components on the same fiber optic-controlled Ammo Load machines as our premium new ammo. These are the same machines used by some of the largest manufacturers in the industry. These machines assure S.A.A.M.I. specifications for priming depth, pressure and overall cartridge length.
FREEDOM MUNITIONS "Like-New" manufacturing process with the new projectile, powder and primer assures factory ammo performance that discriminating shooters expect.

 Gun is in like new condition with approximately 100 rounds fired. This gun was purchased brand new in May and has been taken to the range twice, cleaned thoroughly, and never carried.  I am asking $550.00 for this gun and all accessories. Let's be honest, that is a bargain considering these pistols sell for well into the $600's. I am open to negotiate, but don't waste time with low-ball offers. Not interested in trades, cash only. Let's make a deal! 
 I live just outside of Memphis, TN, and will not travel further than 30 miles. Because of my odd work schedule, meeting time needs to be convenient to me. Buyer must be 18+ and possess Handgun Carry Permit or show valid Driver License. Call or text (901) 412 - 8423 with offers.

title: For Sale:  NEF Pardner Protector 12g custom tactical home defense shotgun
postcontent:
This shotgun is a copy of the Remington 870. Which is a great shotgun... But... Remington seems to have fallen in love with putting plastic parts all over their guns. I'm an all metal reliability guy!  
And the big difference between this shotgun and the remmy is this one holds one more shell than the remmy and is full metal.
I have customized this gun a good bit. 
Specs:
- 18.5" barrel with 3" chamber to accommodate the larger magnum shells. Including but not nearly limited to rifled slugs!  My favorite!  But if you wanna skeet shoot with #8 2-3/4" bird shot shells. They run just fine too. 
- Ive upgraded to an adjustable 6 position stock and pistol grip (Includes a nice recoil pad).
- i've also upgraded to a tri-rail forend. For any lights/lasers you may want to add later as I won't include accessories.
- (2x) 3 shell holders that can mount on either or both sides. 
-  vertical fore-grip.
- (6x) rubber rail covers.
- included is the factory stock and fore-end (hunting type) with buttpad.  
-  I'll also include the fore-end wrench so you can change stocks quickly and simply.
- this gun has a custom camouflage paint job you will not see anywhere else. This gun dawns my favorite self-made camo I've dubbed "urban night viper" this camo plays the shadows and streaks of dim light found in the environment of the interior of a home at night. 
This gun damn near completely disappears in a dark house! 
- all metal construction reliability. 
- I'll include some 00buck and 7-1/2 shot shells. As well. Probably around 30-40 shells.
- if I get my asking price or close I'll include a hard case and a lock. 

This shotgun doesn't quit. Fires every time. And this gun doesn't have the ejector problems that the Remington 870 express it was modeled after is known to have. 
As long as you positively work the pump i doubt this gun will ever fail!  It's certain never failed on me! 
I've put probably around 200 mixed shells through this gun and and cleaned it after every use. To say the least it's in good shape.  The camo is baked on and allowed 24 hours dry time between coats. This will produce a much more durable finish than the average DIY paint can job. 
Basically this has been my home defense shotgun for about 2 years. And it definaty makes you feel safer at night!
I am welcome to a small amount of haggle but I'm not taking $100 off the price either.
I will accept some trades of equal value but i do not have cash to put on top. So anything worth more than $350 won't be accepted unless you're willing to take the loss.

I will want to see a drivers license or some form of valid identification with proof of age. A bill of sale will also need to be signed. But as this is a shotgun... You're only required to be 18 years old.
 I feel these two simple steps will cover both of our asses in the long run.  So don't sweat it.

postcontent:
Make: Smith & Wesson 

Model: Model 625-6 Mountain Gun 

Serial Number: CAL1750 

Year of Manufacture: 1996 

Caliber: .45 Colt 

Action Type: Single Action and Double Action Swing Out Cylinder Revolver 

Markings: The left side of the barrel is marked “.45 COLT”. The yoke cut is marked “CAL1750 / M625”. The yoke is marked “281”. There is a large S&W logo on the right sideplate and the four line “Marcas Registradas” address on the right side of the frame. The right side of the frame is marked “MOUNTAIN GUN”. br> 
Barrel Length: 4” Tapered Light Contour 

Sights / Optics: The revolver is mounted with a pinned black Patridge front sight. There is a micrometer click adjustable rear sight. 

Stock Configuration & Condition: The grips are checkered walnut K Frame Hand Ejector style with silver colored S&W logo medallions and a black Tyler T-grip. There are no chips or cracks in either grip panel. The left panel checkering is good, while the right panel checkering is worn towards the rear. The grips rate in about Very Good to Fine overall condition. These grips are not original to this revolver and were adapted by the previous owner. 

Type of Finish: Stainless Steel 

Finish Originality: All Original 

Bore Condition: The bore is bright and the rifling shallow with evidence of fouling in the forcing cone and down the barrel. There is no erosion evident. The muzzle crown is good. 

Overall Condition: This revolver retains about 90% of its metal finish. There are to small dings, one on the left above the cylinder release and the other on the right side of the frame centered forward of the cylinder. The serrated back strap is mildly distressed. Most of the other use marks should polish out. There are drag marks on the cylinder. The screw heads are sharp and clean. The markings are clear. Overall, this gun rates in about Fine condition. 

Mechanics: The action functions correctly both single action and double action. There is a case colored checkered .400” semi-target hammer and .312” smooth combat trigger. We have not fired this revolver. 

Box, Paperwork & Accessories: There is a blue S&W plastic box with matching end label provided. The bottom of the box is a little scuffed, but otherwise is in Excellent condition. Also provided is the product registration card, instruction manual and S&W handgun grips brochure. 

Our Assessment: The S&W 625-6 Mountain Gun is largely distinguished by its tapered light contour barrel. It was designed to lessen the load for those who want to carry a .45 Colt double action in the field. With its adjustable sights this revolver can be sighted in for a wide variety of loads, from plinkers to bear stoppers. With its all stainless steel construction it is heavy enough to be controllable and light enough to carry for field conditions.

title: For Sale:  38 SPL +P BUFFALO-BARNES LEAD-FREE - 110 gr. BARNES TAC-XP @  1,125 fps - 20 Round Box
postcontent:
http://extreme-impact-ammo.com/index.php?l=product_detail&p=296

 For those wanting a deep penetrating all copper expanding 38SPL+P load, this is it. Depending on individual impact velocity, (barrel lengths and distance to target vary) you can expect between 12 to 14 inches of penetration in flesh and bone.

 Buffalo Bore was able to engineer a flash suppressed powder for this load and therefore the shooter will not be blinded by his own gun fire in low light. This creates a huge tactical advantage as most civilian shootings in the US occur in low light when the criminal element is out and about.
 This load is safe to fire from all 38SPL +P rated and all/any 357 firearms that are in normal operating condition. However, when fired from super light weight alloy J frame revolvers, recoil is stiff. This cartridge is designed so the bullet will not jump crimp when subjected to recoil from firing in super light 12 OZ revolvers, provided you do not subject any cartridge to the recoil of more than six or seven firings.

With great pleasure, we noted that every test gun delivered tiny little groups at 25 yards. It is normal when we observe good accuracy from most test guns and exceptional accuracy from some test guns with any load we are developing, but this load gave exceptional accuracy from every test gun. Most of our adjustable sighted test guns, needed the rear sight raised as this high speed, light weight bullet shot to a lower point of impact than normal loads our guns were already sighted in for, but the groups (accuracy potential) were very small, none-the-less.
